CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 10, 1963, pg. 19, reads: "Banquet- Fraternal leader Herbert Townes (standing behind the wheelbarrow of money) was honored at a testimonial recently at Bethel AME Church. Townes is the 33 Past Grand Master of the Most Worshipful Hiram Grand Lodge, AF&AM.  In front of the table are (left to right) Solomon Coleman, Mrs. Esther Green and Esther Rice.  Second row: Councilman James Jordon, J.B. Williams (New York), Clendon Lawrence (Ohio), Milton Owens, Luther Rice, Herbert Townes, the honoree; Mrs. Catherine Johnson, S.O. Simpson, Prothonotary David B. Roberts, the Rev. J.G.Harris, Mrs. J.F. Little and the Rev. J.F. Little.  in background, J. William Duncan (New York), master of ceremonies, is surrounded by the Grand Officers of Omega Grand Chapter."
TitMainTitle: Members of Hiram Grand Lodge, including Solomon Coleman, Esther Green, and Esther Rice standing on chair, posed in front of banquet table with toy wheelbarrow full of money with Herbert Townes, with men and women standing in background, another version
